baby sleeping tips my m onth old refuses to sleep any where else but with me it takes me minutes a night getting him to sleep and thats only if hes actually sleepy and hes still waking up to be fed i feed him more at night to keep him full but nothing works do you have any tips on getting him to sleep and keeping him asleep i do use baby cereal and it doesnt work it's nice to be wanted so much by someone isn't it it's hard to say no to someone who obviously loves and needs you but that's what you need to do spend more time outside in the afternoon that will make him sleepy establish a bedtime routine so he knows what's coming and is ready to go to bed i always read to my children sometimes sitting by their bed to read to them after they were in bed an mo old may not understand the story but he enjoys hearing you talk he isn't waking because he's hungry he's waking out of habit because he knows you'll come when he cries at night check to be sure he isn't in pain or wet then put him back to bed you may have to listen to him cry for a few nights but he will get the idea that you're not going to pick him up until morning Shaggy dog story Avenue Q The Amber Spyglass Sleep The Shining (film) The Catcher in the Rye Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Characters in the Smurfs Futurama (TV series - season 5) Mattress Ron and Fez Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Daylight saving time Knots Landing The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Apollo 8 Urinary incontinence Odyssey Jon Secada Bon Jovi Delayed sleep phase syndrome Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind About a Boy Narcolepsy Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Patrick Star Breastfeeding Out-of-body experience Humphrey Bogart Hansel und Gretel Miss Saigon Milton H. Erickson Cat Elvis Presley Sin City The Inside Night (book) Pitaten Procrastination Good Morning, Vietnam Lucid dreaming Garfield Slow Train Coming Objects in Space Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 February Marie Antoinette Episodes of Lost (Season 2) 